  gem-c-title--margin-bottom-5">
  <h1 class="gem-c-title__text ">
    Personal information charter
  </h1>
</div>

    </div>
    
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
  <p class="gem-c-lead-paragraph ">
    This personal information charter explains how we look after your information.
  </p>

      
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row ">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
        <div id="contents" class="app-c-contents-list-with-body">
    
        <div class="responsive-bottom-margin">
          
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hmpo-privacy-information-notice">HMPO privacy information notice</a> supplements the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/home-office/about/personal-information-charter">Home Office personal information charter</a>. It explains your rights as an individual when using services provided by Her Majesty’s Passport Office (HMPO) and sets out how HMPO uses personal information provided to them.</p>

<p>You can also find out how to ask for <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/subject-access-request-form">personal data held by HMPO</a>.</p>

<p>The privacy information notice is provided in accordance with data protection legislation which incorporates the General Data Protection Regulations (GDPR) and has been created following the guidance issued by the Information Commissioner’s Office.</p>
</div>
</div>

        </div>

  </div>
